        <body>
            <div type="poem">
                <pb facs="MSIAsheet161"/>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa"><!-- ENTER HANDSHIFT FOR INK -->
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1828-29" script="cursive" medium="pencil"/><name type="astronomical" corresp="#CEPHEUSCONSTELLATION">cepheus</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CEPHEUSGLOSS"/> and <name type="astronomical" corresp="#BOOTES">bootes</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#BOOTESGLOSS"/> now</l>
                    <l>after that the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#APUS">swallow</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#APUSGLOSS"/><ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#SWALLOWTEXTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#MONSMAENALUS">maenalus mountain</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MONSMAENALUSGLOSS"/> next</l>
                    <l>after that the furious <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LYNX">lynx</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LYNXGLOSS"/><ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#LYNXTEXTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>high up there is <name type="astronomical" corresp="#SCORPIO">scorpio</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#SCORPIOGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>after <subst><del rend="strikethrough">that</del><add place="above"><space quantity="6" unit="chars"/>it</add></subst> king <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LEO">leo</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LEOGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CAMELOPARDALIS">cameleopard</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CAMELOPARDALISGLOSS"/> appeareth high</l>
                    <l>next to it the little <name type="astronomical" corresp="#MUSCA">fly</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MUSCAGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#SERPENS">serpent</name> <del rend="strikethrough">serpent</del> <name type="astronomical" corresp="#OPHIUCHUS">serpent <lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>bearer</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#SERPENSGLOSS"/> then<ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#SERPENSTEXTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>next to it the butting <name type="astronomical" corresp="#ARIES">ram</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#ARIESGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#SCUTUM">sobieskis shield</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#SCUTUMGLOSS"/> up there</l>
                    <l>after it the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#AURIGA">charioteer</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#AURIGAGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#TAURUSPONIATOWSKI">bull of poniatowski</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#TAURUSPONIATOWSKIGLOSS"/><lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="21" unit="chars"/>then</l>
                    <l><subst><del rend="strikethrough">then</del><add place="above"><space quantity="3" unit="chars"/>next</add></subst> the very pretty<lb type="runover" rend="above"/><space quantity="13" unit="chars"/><name type="astronomical" corresp="#GRUS">crane</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#GRUSGLOSS"/><ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#GRUSTEXTGLOSS"/><!--"crane" and "then" are written on the same line--></l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#ANTINOUSCONSTELLATION">antinous</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#ANTINOUSGLOSS"/> and <name type="astronomical" corresp="#SAGITTA">arrow</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#SAGITTAGLOSS"/> soon</l>
                    <l>after it<ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#DOWNTEXTGLOSS"/> the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CORONAAUSTRALIS">southern crown</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CORONAAUSTRALISGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#DELPHINUS">dolphin</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#DELPHINUSGLOSS"/> swimming<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>through the air</l>
                    <l>next to it the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#ARA">altar</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#ARAGLOSS"/><ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#GODSFIREGLOSS"/></l>
                    <pb facs="MSIAsheet162"/>
                    <l>the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CANESVENATICI">hounds</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CANESVENATICIGLOSS"/> the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#TAURUS">bull</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#TAURUSGLOSS"/> are<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>seen up there</l>
                    <l>after it the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#ANTLIA">pump of<lb type="runover" rend="above"/><space quantity="18" unit="chars"/>air</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#ANTLIAGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LEOMINOR">lesser lion</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LEOMINORGLOSS"/> next we<lb type="runover" rend="above"/><space quantity="20" unit="chars"/>see</l>
                    <l>next to it the armed <name type="astronomical" corresp="#MUSCAAUSTRALIS">bee</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MUSCAAUSTRALISGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#PERSEUSCONSTELLATION">perseus</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#PERSEUSGLOSS"/> <name type="astronomical" corresp="#PEGASUSCONSTELLATION">pegasus</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#PEGASUSGLOSS"/> then</l>
                    <l>after it the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CHAMAELEON">chamelion</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CHAMAELEONGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#ANDROMEDACONSTELLATION">andromeda</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#ANDROMEDAGLOSS"/> is seen on high</l>
                    <l>then <del rend="strikethrough">then</del> the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#VIRGO">virgin</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#VIRGOGLOSS"/> in<lb type="runover" rend="above"/><space quantity="18" unit="chars"/>the sky</l>
                    <l>ten starred <name type="astronomical" corresp="#TRIANGULUM">triangle</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#TRIANGULUMGLOSS"/> doth appear</l>
                    <l>the horn <del rend="strikethrough">the horn</del> the<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/><name type="astronomical" corresp="#MONOCEROS">unicorn</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MONOCEROSGLOSS"/> doth bear</l>
                    <l>shining in golden light he&#x02BC;s<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="24" unit="chars"/>drest</l>
                    <l>with a horn instead of<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>a towering crest</l>
                    <l>the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LIBRA">scales</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LIBRAGLOSS"/> that nothing<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="6" unit="chars"/>to weigh would bear</l>
                    <l>but yet contain a thous<lb type="runover" rend="above"/><space quantity="17" unit="chars"/>and more</l>
                    <l>farther than that I<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="5" unit="chars"/>could not say</l>
                    <l>more than the <subst><del rend="strikethrough">lofty</del><add place="above"><space quantity="13" unit="chars"/><handShift medium="ink"/>beautiful<handShift medium="pencil"/></add></subst><lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="5" unit="chars"/>milky way</l>
                    <l>the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#SAGITTARIUS">archer</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#SAGITTARIUSGLOSS"/> with his<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="6" unit="chars"/>flying dart</l>
                    <l>I should not think<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="2" unit="chars"/>it would pierce<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="4" unit="chars"/>the heart</l>
                    x<l>the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CANCER">crab</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CANCERGLOSS"/> and the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#GEMINI">twins</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#GEMINIGLOSS"/><lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="3" unit="chars"/>with their clothes of fire</l>
                    <l>I wish I had not <!--illegible--> the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LYRA">lyre</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LYRAGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#TRIANGULUMAUSTRALE">little triangle</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#TRIANGULUMAUSTRALEGLOSS"/> apears <!--sic--> on high</l>
                    <l>and the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CAPRICORNUS">goat</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CAPRICORNUSGLOSS"/> that is formed in the<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="6" unit="chars"/>arched sky</l>
<!--I did not see this section in the ms pages
                    <l>But oh that wonder of them all</l>
                    <l>Which <name type="astronomical" corresp="#MILKYWAY">milky way</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MILKYWAYGLOSS"/> europeans call</l>
                    <l>And which the ancients thought the road</l>
                    <l>Which all their best and bravest trod</l>
                    <l>Unto great <name type="astronomical" corresp="#JUPITER">Jupiters</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#JUPITERGLOSS"/> blest abode</l>-->
                    <l>bright these stars are, beauteous gold</l>
                    <l>but let history unfold</l>
                    <l>her page of learning let<lb type="runover" rend="above"/><space quantity="19" unit="chars"/>us see</l>
                    <l>Whether that is not more<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>bright than thee</l>
                    <l>Een thou O beauteous <name type="astronomical" corresp="#MERCURY">mercury</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MERCURYGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Much better than the brightest<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>star</l>
                    <l>Virtue I will say you<lb type="runover" rend="above"/><space quantity="19" unit="chars"/>are</l>
                    <l>Better than knowledge yes indeed</l>
                    <l>Virtue you <del rend="strikethrough">shall</del><add place="above"><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>should</add> have<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>the lead
                    </l>
                    
                    
                </lg>
            </div>
            
                
           
